waiting for you.

885
00:33:54,350 --> 00:33:55,870
These are for your probation.

886
00:34:00,500 --> 00:34:01,390
They're all

887
00:34:01,870 --> 00:34:02,460
blue.

888
00:34:02,460 --> 00:34:03,540
What's the difference?

889
00:34:05,150 --> 00:34:06,150
Take a look.

890
00:34:06,830 --> 00:34:08,100
This is royal blue.

891
00:34:09,350 --> 00:34:10,350
This is navy blue.

892
00:34:10,950 --> 00:34:12,230
It's obvious.

893
00:34:20,580 --> 00:34:22,500
- Kind of obvious.
- It's obvious.

894
00:34:22,620 --> 00:34:23,460
Get out!

895
00:34:25,460 --> 00:34:26,230
Tell me.

896
00:34:26,790 --> 00:34:29,020
What's the difference

897
00:34:29,020 --> 00:34:31,010
between the blue in summer
and the blue in autumn?

898
00:34:32,230 --> 00:34:33,750
The color is a little darker.

899
00:34:38,390 --> 00:34:39,580
I'm leaving, Director Zhou.

900
00:34:39,950 --> 00:34:40,500
Bye.

901
00:34:40,540 --> 00:34:41,430
- See you.
- See you.

902
00:34:41,430 --> 00:34:42,100
Bye.

903
00:34:43,060 --> 00:34:44,230
You won't see me tomorrow.

904
00:34:44,870 --> 00:34:46,310
I'm going to quit.

905
00:34:46,750 --> 00:34:47,430
What?

906
00:34:47,750 --> 00:34:49,020
Why are you quitting?

907
00:34:49,020 --> 00:34:50,140
What do you mean?

908
00:34:51,500 --> 00:34:52,350
Xiaomao.

909
00:34:54,270 --> 00:34:55,540
I'm going back to get married.

910
00:34:55,830 --> 00:34:56,660
Get married?

911
00:34:57,500 --> 00:34:58,950
You're getting married young?

912
00:34:59,950 --> 00:35:02,870
I've been working here for so long
but still haven't been made permanent.

913
00:35:03,140 --> 00:35:04,980
My girlfriend's been waiting
for me for years.

914
00:35:05,910 --> 00:35:06,950
She told me

915
00:35:06,980 --> 00:35:07,830
to either get married

916
00:35:08,430 --> 00:35:09,140
or break up.

917
00:35:10,500 --> 00:35:11,790
I love her very much.

918
00:35:12,850 --> 00:35:14,100
We already booked the tickets.

919
00:35:14,580 --> 00:35:16,710
I can't make movies with you anymore.

920
00:35:17,020 --> 00:35:17,750
No!

921
00:35:19,740 --> 00:35:20,750
Where's your girlfriend?

922
00:35:21,790 --> 00:35:22,580
Take us to her.

923
00:35:26,060 --> 00:35:27,390
Dear, listen to me.

924
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:29,190
It's too early for you
to go to the airport.

925
00:35:29,190 --> 00:35:30,180
Your flight is at 9 PM.

926
00:35:30,260 --> 00:35:31,870
Wait for me, I'll be at the hotel soon.

927
00:35:31,980 --> 00:35:32,710
Right away.

928
00:35:33,350 --> 00:35:34,750
She has packed her luggage.

929
00:35:34,790 --> 00:35:35,830
Mr. Li, welcome home.

930
00:35:37,950 --> 00:35:39,460
No, you're staying here temporarily?

931
00:35:39,460 --> 00:35:40,660
We have always stayed here.

932
00:35:40,790 --> 00:35:43,020
You're staying at a five-star hotel.

933
00:35:43,020 --> 00:35:43,360
Not bad.

934
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:44,790
It's good to have a staff to clean.

935
00:35:44,790 --> 00:35:46,020
Then why do you keep eating

936
00:35:46,020 --> 00:35:47,020
buns and instant noodles?

937
00:35:47,020 --> 00:35:48,180
A lot of footage to edit.

938
00:35:48,180 --> 00:35:49,220
I don't have time to eat.

939
00:35:49,220 --> 00:35:50,310
Buddy, you're rich.

940
00:35:50,310 --> 00:35:51,230
Why edit footage there?

941
00:35:51,230 --> 00:35:52,060
That's not my money.

942
00:35:52,060 --> 00:35:53,230
It's my dad's money!

943
00:35:53,230 --> 00:35:55,200
Your dad's rich,
so you don't need to work hard!

944
00:36:01,870 --> 00:36:03,100
Do you understand me or not?

945
00:36:07,100 --> 00:36:08,460
If I don't work hard,

946
00:36:09,750 --> 00:36:10,660
I have to go back

947
00:36:10,660 --> 00:36:12,980
to inherit our family's dental clinic!

948
00:36:15,500 --> 00:36:15,910
Mr. Li.

949
00:36:15,980 --> 00:36:16,910
Welcome home.

950
00:36:18,270 --> 00:36:19,060
Li Xiaomao.

951
00:36:21,060 --> 00:36:21,580
Yan.

952
00:36:21,580 --> 00:36:23,180
- Send it to Bengbu, Anhui.
- What?

953
00:36:27,790 --> 00:36:29,350
I brought my colleagues to meet you.

954
00:36:31,950 --> 00:36:32,750
- Hi.
- Hi.

955
00:36:32,750 --> 00:36:33,430
I've met them.

956
00:36:34,350 --> 00:36:35,180
Miss, please stay!

957
00:36:35,310 --> 00:36:36,870
Can you let him stay here?

958
00:36:37,580 --> 00:36:38,350
Yes.

959
00:36:38,420 --> 00:36:39,180
Just break up.

960
00:36:39,180 --> 00:36:39,950
No!

961
00:36:39,950 --> 00:36:41,980
Well... Xiaomao came to Beijing

962
00:36:41,980 --> 00:36:43,460
to make money to support you.

963
00:36:43,460 --> 00:36:44,830
Don't talk nonsense!

964
00:36:45,500 --> 00:36:46,460
She's richer than me.

965
00:36:50,350 --> 00:36:51,580
Can you not get married first?

966
00:36:53,750 --> 00:36:54,660
What do you think?

967
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:02,640
We've been dating for seven years.

968
00:37:03,039 --> 00:37:05,329
I need to take on the responsibility
that I should bear.

969
00:37:05,560 --> 00:37:07,610
Can you guys get engaged first?

970
00:37:07,610 --> 00:37:10,170
We're already engaged!

971
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:16,150
Maybe I shouldn't have come to Beijing.

972
00:37:16,630 --> 00:37:17,990
I'm too selfish.

973
00:37:21,110 --> 00:37:22,920
Didn't you bring so many colleagues
to meet me

974
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:24,760
because you want me
to give you some face?

975
00:37:26,030 --> 00:37:26,630
Okay.

976
00:37:26,960 --> 00:37:28,240
I'll give you face.

977
00:37:30,880 --> 00:37:31,630
I know

978
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:34,110
you want to stay in Beijing
to make movies.

979
00:37:34,720 --> 00:37:35,150
Right?

980
00:37:36,760 --> 00:37:37,590
Let's...

981
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:42,920
Break up.

982
00:37:42,920 --> 00:37:45,470
- Okay!
- Okay!

983
00:37:45,510 --> 00:37:46,550
Well...

984
00:37:48,590 --> 00:37:49,630
Break up?

985
00:37:49,630 --> 00:37:50,840
Listen well.

986
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:55,550
You look pretty handsome today.

987
00:38:16,280 --> 00:38:16,960
Xiaomao.

988
00:38:20,990 --> 00:38:22,190
Let me tell you a secret.

989
00:38:24,840 --> 00:38:25,880
Didn't you say before

990
00:38:25,880 --> 00:38:26,880
that Daji and I

991
00:38:27,510 --> 00:38:28,990
don't look like a couple?

992
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:32,240
Indeed, we think so too.

993
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:34,880
Because Daji has broken up

994
00:38:35,030 --> 00:38:36,800
with me half a year ago.

995
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:40,590
Break up?

996
00:38:44,670 --> 00:38:48,070
She left me and Beijing half a year ago.

997
00:38:50,190 --> 00:38:53,840
I think she couldn't hold on any longer
in the relationship.

998
00:38:57,150 --> 00:38:58,240
But I can't let her go.

999
00:38:59,440 --> 00:39:01,190
Just like how we can't let go of movies.

1000
00:39:02,330 --> 00:39:04,110
Why was she willing
to come back with you?

1001
00:39:07,030 --> 00:39:07,920
I don't know either.

1002
00:39:14,590 --> 00:39:15,400
Yan!

1003
00:39:16,800 --> 00:39:18,440
Miss Yan!

1004
00:39:19,320 --> 00:39:21,800
Miss Yan!

1005
00:39:22,150 --> 00:39:24,110
Yan!

1006
00:39:24,920 --> 00:39:27,360
Miss Yan!

1007
00:39:28,510 --> 00:39:30,470
Yan!

1008
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:42,150
Miss Yan!

1009
00:39:43,070 --> 00:39:44,960
I know why you want to leave.

1010
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:47,440
I understand you

1011
00:39:48,240 --> 00:39:49,630
because we're the same.

1012
00:39:49,760 --> 00:39:51,190
How are we the same?

1013
00:39:51,400 --> 00:39:55,360
We both fell in love
with a boy who loves movies.

1014
00:39:56,670 --> 00:39:58,280
We broke up before.

1015
00:39:58,470 --> 00:40:00,720
The reason
I was willing to come back with him

1016
00:40:02,320 --> 00:40:04,550
is because he's different from others.

1017
00:40:05,030 --> 00:40:06,360
He has a dream

1018
00:40:06,670 --> 00:40:07,800
and loves movies.

1019
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:11,470
He shines!

1020
00:40:29,960 --> 00:40:30,760
Miss Yan!

1021
00:40:31,960 --> 00:40:32,760
The five of us

1022
00:40:32,760 --> 00:40:34,360
became friends

1023
00:40:34,760 --> 00:40:36,670
because we have a common dream.

1024
00:40:37,190 --> 00:40:39,030
We're going to make movies in Beijing.

1025
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:41,280
Every one of us is indispensable.

1026
00:40:41,630 --> 00:40:44,360
I can see that you're the same as us.

1027
00:40:44,620 --> 00:40:45,760
Otherwise, you wouldn't have

1028
00:40:45,760 --> 00:40:47,380
waited for him in Beijing
for four years.

1029
00:40:47,590 --> 00:40:49,280
Li Xiaomao didn't let you down.

1030
00:40:49,630 --> 00:40:51,550
We're very close to making movies.

1031
00:40:52,280 --> 00:40:54,070
Li Xiaomao is a brave man.

1032
00:40:54,470 --> 00:40:55,880
A man with dreams.

1033
00:40:56,110 --> 00:40:58,110
People with dreams are worthy of love!

1034
00:40:58,670 --> 00:41:02,630
People with dreams shine!

1035
00:41:03,670 --> 00:41:05,030
- Stay here!
- Stay here!

1036
00:41:05,550 --> 00:41:09,030
- Let's make movies together!
- Let's make movies together!

1037
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:10,360
Stop talking.

1038
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:12,920
Yan!

1039
00:41:13,720 --> 00:41:14,760
I love you!

1040
00:41:15,720 --> 00:41:17,320
Please don't leave!

1041
00:41:24,920 --> 00:41:26,400
Why did she leave anyway?

1042
00:41:34,880 --> 00:41:36,440
It's okay, Xiaomao.

1043
00:41:36,800 --> 00:41:37,990
You tried your best, Xiaomao.

1044
00:41:39,470 --> 00:41:40,990
What should I do?

1045
00:41:50,150 --> 00:41:51,320
Xiaomao.

1046
00:42:13,440 --> 00:42:15,240
(Impressing others with dreams)

1047
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:17,840
(sounds like a joke now.)

1048
00:42:18,630 --> 00:42:19,840
(But many years later,)

1049
00:42:20,470 --> 00:42:22,510
(the me who's been worn down by reality)

1050
00:42:23,280 --> 00:42:26,240
(misses that shining era)

1051
00:42:26,880 --> 00:42:28,470
(and those shining people even more.)

1052
00:42:28,470 --> 00:42:30,920
We can make movies now.

1053
00:42:31,150 --> 00:42:32,030
Let's make movies!

1054
00:42:32,030 --> 00:42:33,320
Zhou Shui!

1055
00:42:35,510 --> 00:42:36,550
I get it now.

1056
00:42:37,510 --> 00:42:39,030
I came back to Beijing this time

1057
00:42:40,280 --> 00:42:42,240
to help you make movies.

1058
00:42:43,110 --> 00:42:46,510
I'm here to help you
realize your movie dream!

1059
00:42:47,470 --> 00:42:48,510
Thank you, Daji!

1060
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:56,240
If you don't let me down,

1061
00:42:57,470 --> 00:42:58,590
I won't let you down either.

1062
00:43:31,730 --> 00:43:33,070
Is it worth it?

1063
00:43:33,310 --> 00:43:37,080
From having nothing to having nothing

1064
00:43:38,660 --> 00:43:40,160
Is it worth it?

1065
00:43:40,550 --> 00:43:44,400
To turn back at every crossroads

1066
00:43:45,960 --> 00:43:47,010
Is it worth it?

1067
00:43:47,580 --> 00:43:51,370
Swearing to become the sea,
not just a river

1068
00:43:52,820 --> 00:43:54,240
Is it worth it?

1069
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:58,830
That night,
the wine was finished with just one sip

1070
00:43:59,870 --> 00:44:01,540
Do you dare?

1071
00:44:01,700 --> 00:44:05,490
When having nothing, I don't frown

1072
00:44:07,020 --> 00:44:08,530
Do you dare?

1073
00:44:08,610 --> 00:44:12,880
Once I decide to start,
I hold your hand tightly

1074
00:44:13,890 --> 00:44:15,810
Do you dare?

1075
00:44:15,880 --> 00:44:19,420
Even in the coldest winter,
we feel it on the ice

1076
00:44:21,080 --> 00:44:22,750
Do you dare?

1077
00:44:22,850 --> 00:44:26,980
Striving for an outlet
in reality and love

1078
00:44:28,340 --> 00:44:33,570
Only to realize when we drift apart

1079
00:44:33,650 --> 00:44:38,610
We mistook that day for forever

1080
00:44:38,840 --> 00:44:42,480
Time passes, bidding farewell to youth

1081
00:44:42,510 --> 00:44:47,610
Luckily, we have been brave
ever since we met

1082
00:44:47,790 --> 00:44:53,010
Perhaps that day means forever

1083
00:44:53,530 --> 00:44:58,480
Outrunning time,
leaving the past behind

1084
00:45:00,980 --> 00:45:04,480
Is it worth it?

1085
00:45:04,590 --> 00:45:08,050
Do you dare?

1086
00:45:08,080 --> 00:45:14,800
The love that's worth it, be brave

1087
00:45:15,960 --> 00:45:21,150
Later, the ocean drifted far away

1088
00:45:21,330 --> 00:45:26,440
Even the waves grew tired

1089
00:45:26,540 --> 00:45:30,170
The coldest days once burned
like blazing flames

1090
00:45:30,190 --> 00:45:36,250
Perhaps someday,
we will look back on the past

1091
00:45:36,990 --> 00:45:40,400
Ideals and vows.
How passionate they were

1092
00:45:40,490 --> 00:45:46,530
Once, there was a moment so vivid

